PREAMBLE
The goals of the Open Font License (OFL) are to stimulate worldwide development
of collaborative font projects, to support the font creation efforts of academic
and linguistic communities, and to provide a free and open framework in which
fonts may be shared and improved in partnership with others.

The fonts are free to use, modify, and redistribute under the following conditions:

1. Neither the Font Software nor any of its individual components, in Original or
   Modified Versions, may be sold by itself.

2. Original or Modified Versions of the Font Software may be bundled, redistributed
   and/or sold with any software, provided that each copy contains the above
   copyright notice and this license.

3. No Modified Version of the Font Software may use the Reserved Font Name(s)
   unless explicit written permission is granted by the corresponding Copyright Holder.

4. The Font Software, modified or unmodified, in part or in whole, must be distributed
   entirely under this license, and must not be distributed under any other license.

5. The Font Software may not be used to create derivative works that infringe upon
   the copyrights of the original authors.

TERMINATION
This license becomes null and void if any of the above conditions are not met.

